L: http://www.myexperiment.org/workflows/3262.html',1,1,0,1,1,1,'2013-03-19 14:56:08','2013-10-11 09:42:00'),(3921,'RetrieveSolarMonitorURLS',2128,2612,'\n\nThis workflow has been downloaded from the myExperiment web site. \nURL: http://www.myexperiment.org/workflows/945.html',1,1,1,1,1,0,'2013-03-19 14:59:59','2013-08-12 14:26:46'),(3922,'RetrieveVOTableEvts',1352,3204,'\n\nThis workflow has been downloaded from the myExperiment web site. \nURL: http://www.myexperiment.org/workflows/945.html',1,1,1,1,1,1,'2013-03-19 14:59:59','2013-10-09 09:20:56'),(3923,'PathwaysandGeneannotationsforQTLregion',2360,2614,'This workflow searches for genes which reside in a QTL (Quantitative Trait Loci) region in the mouse, Mus musculus. The workflow requires an input of: a chromosome name or number; a QTL start base pair position; QTL end base pair position. Data is then extracted from BioMart to annotate each of the genes found in this region. The Entrez and UniProt identifiers are then sent to KEGG to obtain KEGG gene identifiers. The KEGG gene identifiers are then used to searcg for pathways in the KEGG pathway database.\n\nThis workflow has been downloaded from the myExperiment web site. \nURL: http://www.myexperiment.org/workflows/16.html',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2013-03-19 15:09:38','2013-08-08 12:32:18'),(3924,'GiulianoTestWF',2358,2703,'test',1,1,1,1,1,0,'2013-03-19 15:10:19','2013-08-15 12:44:52'),(3925,'karolis_eigelisWF',2352,2402,'Test workflow created by Karolis Eigelis',1,0,1,0,0,0,'2013-03-19 15:16:21','2013-08-12 11:07:29'),(3926,'nunoferreira-WF',2361,2402,'SHIWA WF repo tutorial - point 5',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2013-03-19 15:24:03','2013-03-19 15:24:03'),(3927,'xretrievingsolarmonitorurlsforvotableevents',2151,2615,'\n\nThis workflow has been downloaded from the myExperiment web site. \nURL: http://www.myexperiment.org/workflows/945.html',1,1,0,1,1,0,'2013-03-19 15:54:11','2013-08-12 14:27:43'),(3928,'GabPrepareForKepler',2128,2402,'This is the description of the abstractWorkflow',1,1