ld, containing all the genes of the strains being compared. This super genome building step starts with the first genome and searches for homologous genes in the other genomes. Genes that do not have a homologous gene in the super genome are added to this growing super genome. Eventually this super genome will contain the union of all genes of all compared strains. The user can set the minimal query coverage and the minimal homology to determine if a gene is \'equal\' to a gene in the super genome or should be added as a new gene. In a second step all genes of all strains are compared to this super genome, counted and hierarchically clustered. Again the user can set the minimal query coverage and minimal homology to determine if two genes are homologous.'),(63976,3207,'definition','diffgenomes-SSP-vlemed.gwendia'),(63977,3207,'graph','workflow.png'),(63978,3207,'language','gwendia'),(63979,3207,'rights','AMC'),(63980,3207,'licence','GPLv3'),(63981,3207,'keywords','homologous genes,genome'),(63982,3207,'uuid','100f0cba-34f4-4a64-82d7-3230e6ed2717'),(63983,3207,'execution.deployer.email','v.korkhov@amc.uva.nl'),(63984,3207,'execution.deployer.username','vladimir'),(63985,3207,'execution.engGemlcaId','GIB-MoteurEngine-Vlemed'),(63986,3207,'execution.maxParallelism','100'),(63987,3207,'execution.maxWallTime','1000'),(63988,3207,'execution.parameters.para0001.cmdLine','true'),(63989,3207,'execution.parameters.para0001.defaultValue','diffgenomes.inputs'),(63990,3207,'execution.parameters.para0001.file','true'),(63991,3207,'execution.parameters.para0001.fixed','false'),(63992,3207,'execution.parameters.para0001.input','true'),(63993,3207,'execution.parameters.para0001.switchName',' '),(63994,3207,'execution.parameters.para0001.title','inputs.xml'),(63995,3207,'execution.parameters.para0001.type','CUSTOM'),(63996,3207,'execution.parameters.para0002.cmdLine','false'),(63997,3207,'execution.parameters.para0002.defaultValue','STDOUT'),(63998,3207,'execution.parameters.para0002